{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1997 |Team=Washington State Cougars |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Pacific-10 Conference |ShortConference=Pac-10 |Division= |CoachRank=9 |APRank=9 |Record=10-2-0 |ConfRecord=7-1-0 |HeadCoach=[[Mike Price]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach=[[Bill Doba]] |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Martin Stadium]] |Champion=Pacific Ten champions |BowlTourney=[[1998 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult=Loss, 16-21, vs. [[1997 Michigan Wolverines football team|Michigan]] }} {{1997 Pacific-10 football standings}} The '''1997 Washington State Cougars football team''' represented [[Washington State University]] during the [[1997 NCAA Division I-A football season|1997 NCAA college football season]]. The Cougars were led by ninth-year head coach [[Mike Price]] and played their home games at [[Martin Stadium]] in [[Pullman, Washington|Pullman]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]].
